<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="K_7793" type="Brief"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Trevenen James Holland an Alfred Escher, London, Mittwoch, 03. April 1872</title></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>Digitale Briefedition Alfred Escher, Zürich: Alfred Escher-Stiftung.</p></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><msDesc><msIdentifier><institution>SBB Historic</institution><idno>VGB_GB_SBBGB03_001</idno></msIdentifier></msDesc><bibl type="printed"/></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><textClass><keywords scheme="http://briefedition.alfred-escher.ch/keywords"><term>Tunnelbau</term><term>Gotthardtunnel</term><term>Eisenbahngesellschaften Offerten</term></keywords></textClass><correspDesc><correspAction type="sent"><persName key="Holland Trevenen James" type="addressee">Trevenen James Holland</persName><persName key="Escher (vom Glas) Alfred" type="sender">Alfred Escher</persName><placeName>London</placeName><date when="1872-04-03">03. April 1872</date></correspAction><correspAction type="received"><placeName>Luzern</placeName></correspAction><correspContext><ref type="previous" target="B2607"/><ref type="next" target="B7714"/><ref type="next-in-corresp" target="B7752"/><ref type="previous-in-corresp" target="B4610"/><ptr type="context" target="4610 7793 7752 4611 7795 7796"/></correspContext></correspDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><front>
      
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7793_p1"><note type="addendum" xml:id="K_7793_c0">Auf der ersten Briefseite unten wurde der Brief übersetzt. Die Übersetzung ist durchgestrichen und nicht lesbar.</note><lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <hi rend="printed">THE PATENT  <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>TUNNELING
        <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>&amp; MINING MACHINE
        <lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>COMPANY.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>LIMITED</hi>
        </p>
      
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7793_p2"><lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>
          <del><hi rend="printed">8, Old Jewry</hi></del>
          <add>18, Finsburg Circus</add>, <hi rend="printed"><placeName key="London (UK)">London</placeName>, <choice><abbr>E. C.</abbr><expan>Eastern Central (östlicher Stadtteil)</expan></choice> </hi></p>
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7793_p3"><lb xml:id="p1-l7"/><date when="1872-04-03">
            <choice><abbr>3<hi rend="sup">d</hi> </abbr><expan>third (drittens)</expan></choice> April <hi rend="printed">187</hi>2</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7793_p4"><lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>From Major T. J. Holland <choice><abbr>C. B.</abbr><expan>Companion of The Most Honourable Order of the Bath</expan></choice><note type="transcript">Abkürzung verifiziert CH, 15.08.2014</note> <lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>Chairman</p>
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7793_p5"><lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>To The Chairman
        <lb xml:id="p1-l11"/><choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Sankt / Sanct / Saint (heilig)</expan></choice> Gothard Railway <choice><abbr>Co.</abbr><expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan></choice> <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/><placeName key="Luzern (Stadt)">Lucerne</placeName> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7793_p6"><lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>Sir</p> </div>
    </front><body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7793_p7"><lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>In case the <rs>letter<ref type="letter" target="K_4610"/></rs> I addressed
        <lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>you on the <date when="1872-03-01"><choice><abbr>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> </abbr><expan>first (erstens)</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>ult<hi rend="sup">o</hi> </abbr><expan>ultimo (letzten [Monats])</expan></choice></date> should not have
        <lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>reached you I beg to attach a
        <lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>copy, and shall be glad to hear
        <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>from you in reply as this Company
        <lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>in conjunction with <choice><abbr>Mon<hi rend="sup">sr</hi> </abbr><expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan></choice> <persName key="Towler John">John Towler</persName> &amp; <choice><abbr>Co</abbr><expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan></choice> <lb xml:id="p1-l20"/>of Leeds will be ready to enter at once
        <lb xml:id="p1-l21"/>into a Contract with your Company
        <lb xml:id="p1-l22"/>on advantageous terms to you in
        <lb xml:id="p1-l23"/>regard to time and cost for making
        <lb xml:id="p1-l24"/>the borings you may require through
        <lb xml:id="p1-l25"/>Mont <placeName key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">St. Gothard</placeName>.</p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7793_p8"><lb xml:id="p1-l26"/>Another copy of the extract
        <lb xml:id="p1-l27"/>from the Report of the Minister
            <lb xml:id="p1-l28"/>of Public Works of <placeName key="Frankreich">France</placeName> relating
        <lb xml:id="p1-l29"/>to this Companys Rock-boring
        <lb xml:id="p1-l30"/>Machine is attached.</p>
    </body><back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7793_p9"><lb xml:id="p1-l31"/>I am, Sir
        <lb xml:id="p1-l32"/>Yours Very truly</p>
      </div>
      <div type="signature">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7793_p10"><lb xml:id="p1-l33"/>Trev. J. Holland
        <lb xml:id="p1-l34"/>Chairman</p> </div>
    </back></text></TEI>